104. Formulate a PHP program to open a text file and print the nth line in the text file if then'th line
does not exist print 'no data'.

ANSWER
<?php
// Define the file path and the line number to fetch
$filename = "sample.txt";  // Make sure this file exists in the same folder
$n = 3; // For example: print the 3rd line (change as needed)

// Check if the file exists
if (file_exists($filename)) {
    // Read all lines into an array
    $lines = file($filename, FILE_IGNORE_NEW_LINES);

    // Check if the n-th line exists (array index is n-1)
    if (isset($lines[$n - 1])) {
        echo "Line $n: " . htmlspecialchars($lines[$n - 1]);
    } else {
        echo "no data";
    }
} else {
    echo "File not found.";
}
?>

OUTPUT
File not found.

